[SN]TITLE[SN]
Brass band president Brian Croxton in suspected hit-and-run

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Tributes have been paid to a former president of a brass band club who died in a suspected hit-and-run crash outside the club.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Brian Croxton, 77, was found with serious injuries outside the Brass Band Club in Sandy Lane, Royton in Oldham, at about 23:00 GMT on Thursday.
He was taken to hospital where he died.
Paying tribute to him, his family said he had been president of the club for more than 10 years and "his life revolved" around it.
Greater Manchester Police believe Mr Croxton may have been hit by a car whose driver failed to stop afterwards.
Officers have appealed for any witnesses to contact them.
